FBIS4-62203 "drsov093_e_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Tu-22 Pilots Grounded Due To Defense Ministry `Suspicions' Tu-22 Pilots Grounded Due To Defense Ministry `Suspicions' LD1205212594 Moscow NTV in Russian 1800 GMT 12 May 94 LD1205212594 Moscow NTV Russian BFN [Text] [Announcer Presenter Osokin] In Ukraine, pilots of Black Sea Fleet missile-carrying Tu-22 aircraft are complaining they are not being allowed to fly. They say the explanation is the persistent suspicion of the local authorities. The Ukrainian Ministry of Defense says the pilots are preparing to fly the aircraft away to Russia. With the directness characteristic of the military, the aircrew call these statements complete and utter lies.
